# ğŸ§  HR Analytics-Employee Attrition Prediction

## ğŸ“Œ Overview
This project predicts employee attrition using HR analytics and machine learning. It identifies key risk factors and helps HR teams take proactive retention measures.

## ğŸ“‚ Dataset Features
- **Demographics**: Age, Gender, Marital Status
- **Job Details**: Department, Job Role, Years at Company, OverTime
- **Satisfaction Metrics**: Job Satisfaction, Environment Satisfaction, Work-Life Balance
- **Compensation**: Monthly Income, Percent Salary Hike
- **Target**: Attrition (Yes/No)

## âš™ï¸ Workflow

### 1. Data Preprocessing
- Handled missing values and outliers
- Encoded categorical variables (Label Encoding, One-Hot Encoding)
- Scaled features using StandardScaler

### 2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Visualized attrition trends by department, age group, and job role
- Used heatmaps and boxplots to identify key drivers
- Found OverTime and low satisfaction as major risk factors

### 3. Model Building
- Trained classifiers: Logistic Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost
- Evaluated using Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-score, ROC-AUC

### 4. Insights & Business Impact
- OverTime, low Job Satisfaction, and poor Work-Life Balance strongly correlate with attrition
- Suggested HR interventions for high-risk segments
- Enabled data-driven retention strategies

